items.title: Indians punch playoff ticket with Angels' loss
items.summary: Hours after Cleveland extended its American League-record winning streak to 22 wins with a 3-2, 10-inning walk-off victory over the Royals, the Indians reserved a spot in the 2017 postseason. That is the first step toward the Tribe's goal of returning to and winning the World Series, and it was clinched when the Astros defeated the Angels in Anaheim.

items.title: At long last, happy Astros heading home
items.summary: After a grueling three-week stretch in which they played 16 of 19 games on the road -- including three that were relocated to St. Petersburg because of Hurricane Harvey -- the Astros are coming home to stay a while. And they're in the mood to party.

items.title: Bauer, Tribe go for 23rd straight W on MLB.TV
items.summary: The American League-leading Indians put their 22-game win streak on the line tonight when they host the contending Royals as part of today's full schedule of Major League action streaming live on MLB.TV.
